Here is a JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7F:
```javascript
for (let i = 0; i <= 7F; i++) {
  let charCode = String.fromCharCode(i);
  let hexCode = charCode.toString(16).toUpperCase();
  console.log(`ASCII character: ${charCode}, Hexadecimal code: ${hexCode}`);
}
```
This program uses a for loop to iterate through the numbers from 0 to 7F, and for each number it generates the corresponding ASCII character using the String.fromCharCode() method, and then converts the character code to hexadecimal using the toString(16) method and converts it to uppercase using the toUpperCase() method. The results are printed out to the console using the console.log() method.
